The accident involved a landing and other weather encounter.
The accident involved an approach-VFR go-around with abnormal runway contact as the defining event.
The accident involved an approach-VFR go-around with collision with terrain/object (non-CFIT).
The pilot held a Sport Pilot certificate.
The pilot was 58 years old.
The pilot had an Airplane Rating for Single-engine land.
The pilot had no Other Aircraft Rating(s).

The pilot had no Instructor Rating(s).
The pilot's Medical Certification was Sport pilot Without waivers/limitations.
The pilot was not an Occupational Pilot.
The pilot's last Flight Review or Equivalent was on June 30, 2013.
The pilot had an estimated 285 hours of total flight time in all aircraft.
The pilot had an estimated 260 hours of total flight time in this make and model.
The pilot occupied the Left seat.
The pilot used a 3-point restraint.
No Second Pilot was present.
No Toxicology was performed on the pilot.
The aircraft was an EVEKTOR-AEROTECHNIK AS make.
The aircraft model/series was SPORTSTAR.
The aircraft was manufactured in 2007.
The aircraft had registration number N821EV.
The aircraft category was Airplane.

The aircraft Serial Number was 20070821.
The aircraft had Tricycle landing gear.
The aircraft had 2 seats.

The aircraft had 10 hours since the last inspection.
The aircraft had 685 total airframe hours at the time of accident.
The aircraft had an Emergency Locator Transmitter (ELT) installed.
The aircraft engine manufacturer was Rotax.
The aircraft engine model/series was 912 ULS.
The aircraft engine had 100 Horsepower rated power.
BAAR RONALD was the registered owner of the aircraft.
BAAR RONALD was the operator of the aircraft.
